{{Politics of Zambia}}
The '''Ministry of Information and Broadcasting Services''' is a [[Ministry (government department)|ministry]] in [[Zambia]]. It is headed by the Minister of Information and Broadcasting Services.
The ministry controls two publicly-owned newspapers, the [[Times of Zambia]] and the [[Zambia Daily Mail]], and has a seat on the board of the [[Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation]].<ref>[http://www.mibs.gov.zm/?q=about_us About us] Ministry of Information and Broadcasting Services</ref>
==History== The Information and Broadcasting Services portfolio was combined with [[Ministry of Tourism and Arts|Tourism]] during the 1960s, before the two were split.
